<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="sin" id="sin">sin</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Sintaxe:
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cmath&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">double</span> <span class="kw3">sin</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> arg <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>

A função sin devolve o seno de <code>arg</code>, onde <code>arg</code> é dado em radianos. O valor
devolvido de sin estará no intervalo [-1,1]. Se <code>arg</code> for infinito, sin
irá devolver NaN e provocará uma excepção de vírgula flutuante.
</p>

<p>
O C++ também fornece as seguintes formas sobre-carregadas (overload):

</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cmath&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">float</span> <span class="kw3">sin</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">float</span> arg <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span> <span class="co1">// igual a sinf() em C99</span>
    <span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> <span class="kw3">sin</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> arg <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span> <span class="co1">// igual a sinl() em C99</span></pre>
<p>
Uma maneira possível de <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Small_angle_approximation" class="urlextern" title="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Small_angle_approximation"  rel="nofollow">aproximar a função seno usando séries de Taylor</a> tira vantagem do facto de que sin(x) = x - x<sup>3</sup>/3! + x<sup>5</sup>/5! - x<sup>7</sup>/7! + …, produzindo o seguinte código:
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp"><span class="kw4">long</span> factrl<span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="kw4">int</span> n<span class="br0">&#41;</span> <span class="br0">&#123;</span>
  <span class="kw4">long</span> la <span class="sy1">=</span> <span class="nu0">1</span><span class="sy4">;</span>
  <span class="kw1">for</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">int</span> i <span class="sy1">=</span> <span class="nu0">2</span><span class="sy4">;</span> i <span class="sy1">&lt;=</span> n<span class="sy4">;</span> i<span class="sy2">++</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span> la <span class="sy2">*</span><span class="sy1">=</span> i<span class="sy4">;</span>
  <span class="kw1">return</span> la<span class="sy4">;</span>
<span class="br0">&#125;</span>
